# Multi-Agent Coordination Protocol

You are NOT the only agent working on this project. Hermes (another AI agent) may also be building sites, deploying, and modifying `leads.csv`. **Assume the state can change between your sessions.**

## Session Start (MANDATORY — do this first)

1. Read `C:\Users\Humberto\website-projects\AGENTS.md` — project rules, quality standards, pipeline
2. Read `C:\Users\Humberto\website-projects\development_log.md` — what other agents did recently
3. Read `C:\Users\Humberto\website-projects\leads.csv` — current lead statuses (may have changed)

## CLAIMING Protocol — PREVENT DOUBLE-WORK

Before building a site for ANY lead:

1. **Check leads.csv** — if status is NOT `new`, skip it (someone already handled it)
2. **Check development_log.md** — if another agent claimed it today, skip it
3. **Mark as claimed** — update the lead's status in leads.csv from `new` to `in_progress` BEFORE starting work
4. **Log the claim** — append to development_log.md: `### Claimed: [business name] ([slug])`

If another agent already claimed it (status is `in_progress`), pick a different lead.

## After Completing Work

1. **Update leads.csv** — set status to `new` (demo built), add `demo_url`, update `notes`
2. **Regenerate tracker** — run `cd C:\Users\Humberto\website-projects && python regenerate-tracker.py`
3. **Append to development_log.md** — use this format:

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — [Project Name]

### Summary
[One line — what was accomplished]

### Actions
- [Action with result]
- [Action with result]

### Key Decisions
- [Decision and why]

### Files Changed
- `path` — what changed

### Blockers / Notes
- [Anything pending]
```

4. **Push to GitHub** — after CSV and tracker changes

## Development Log Rules

- **Append only** — never overwrite or delete previous entries
- **Read fresh every session** — don't rely on memory
- **One date block per day** — if you work on multiple projects, give each its own `### [Project]` subsection under the same date
- **Log everything** — research, decisions, deployments, errors, blockers

## Conflict Prevention Checklist

Before touching any file, ask:
- Did another agent modify this since I last read it? (check log + CSV timestamps)
- Is the lead I want still `new`? (re-read CSV)
- Am I about to overwrite someone else's work? (check git status, re-read files)
